main event: An unidentified object was sighted by a Navy aircraft over the Azores on January 19, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling at 195 knots at an altitude of 30,000 feet., The observation lasted for 5 to 10 minutes., The object was seen for only 1 second before it disappeared back into cloud cover., The sighting occurred at coordinates 8230N 3215W., The report concludes that the object is probably an aircraft based on its straight flight path and duration.
